quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  20,105,"They ask thee concerning the Mountains: say, \"My Lord will uproot them and scatter them as dust"
  20,106,He will leave them as plains smooth and level
  20,107,Nothing crooked or curved wilt thou see in their place
  20,108,"On that Day will they follow the Caller (straight): no crookedness (can they show) him: all sounds shall humble themselves in the Presence of (God) Most Gracious: nothing shalt thou hear but the tramp of their feet (as they march)"
  20,109,On that Day shall no intercession avail except for those for whom permission has been granted by (God) Most Gracious and whose word is acceptable to Him
  20,110,"He knows what (appears to His creatures as) before or after or behind them: but they shall not compass it with their knowledge"
  20,111,"(All) faces shall be humbled before (Him) - the Living, the Self-Subsisting, Eternal: hopeless indeed will be the man that carries iniquity (on his back)"
  20,112,"But he who works deeds of righteousness, and has faith, will have no fear of harm nor of any curtailment (of what is his due)"
  20,113,"Thus have We sent this down - an arabic Qur'an - and explained therein in detail some of the warnings, in order that they may fear God, or that it may cause their remembrance (of Him)"
  20,114,"High above all is God, the King, the Truth! Be not in haste with the Qur'an before its revelation to thee is completed, but say, \"O my Lord! advance me in knowledge"
  20,115,"We had already, beforehand, taken the covenant of Adam, but he forgot: and We found on his part no firm resolve"